fields.description:
When you modify a file in git and add a new line to the end of the file, Git gives you a useful indication that this was the change that was made.

{code}
-});
\ No newline at end of file
+});
{code}

This is very useful context in a pull request, as you (probably) want to ensure that all changes don&#x27;t remove new lines from the end of file, which is a gold standard for source files.

So, would be nice if this context was visible in PRs so you don&#x27;t need to go check the branch out and inspect the file to confirm.
